Create a s3 bucket (acl disable) and add policy

policy

-------

{

    "Version": "2012-10-17",

    "Statement": [

        {

            "Sid": "PublicReadForGetBucketObjects",

            "Effect": "Allow",

            "Principal": "*",

            "Action": "s3:GetObject",

            "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::<bucket name>/*"

        }

    ]

}

enable the static website hosting and add index.html in the index documents 

-------

create a git repo 

Go to setting and add secret credentials(AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID,  AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY)

go to repo and add file with the name .github/workflows/main.yml

name: Deploy to AWS S3

on:

  push:

    branches:

      - main
 
jobs:

  deploy:

    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
 
    steps:

      - name: Checkout

        uses: actions/checkout@v1
 
      - name: Configure AWS Credentials

        uses: aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials@v1

        with:

          aws-access-key-id: ${{ secrets.AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID }}

          aws-secret-access-key: ${{ secrets.AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY }}

          aws-region: us-east-1
 
      - name: Deploy static site to S3 bucket

        run: aws s3 sync . s3://<bucket-name> --delete

-----

copy the link of s3 bucket and paste to find the content of index.html
 
